  "why": "The paper explicitly designs AutoDAN to produce semantically meaningful, fluent (i.e., plausible) jailbreak prompts and uses LLM-based diversification and synonym/momentum-based word replacement to preserve meaning at each mutation step (e.g., using an LLM to ‘revise’ sentences and using LLM-based mutation because it “preserve[s] the global meaning”). However, the method does not describe any explicit mechanism that measures or bounds cumulative distortion relative to the original prototype across multiple iterations (no distance-from-seed bound, no cumulative perturbation budget, nor an explicit constraint enforcing closeness to the original seed across generations). Termination is based on max iterations or refusal-keyword checks rather than an explicit cumulative-plausibility control. Thus AutoDAN enforces plausibility per-step but does not explicitly control cumulative distortion across repeated mutations.",
